<p>November 1917<br/>Wednesday 21<br/>Very cold.<br/>Started for Jerusalem road up through steep hills<br/>Halted on side of one of the stoney hills. Olive trees everywhere.<br/>Great number of wells at Saris where we watered. Stayed all night.<br/>Village half mile farther on called Enab Converted into hospital.</p>
<p>Thursday 22<br/>Still camped on hill below Saris.<br/>"B"squdn started on outpost or reserve and infantry. Camped in rocky slope of hill near Indian cavalry.<br/>Very cold at night.</p>
